main event: A witness observed multiple bright objects in the night sky over Des Plaines, Illinois, on July 1, 1965.
interesting points: The objects appeared stationary or moving slowly, with varying brightness and a pulsing type of light,The witness observed the objects for about one hour, with additional light flashes occurring to the south of the main object,The objects were seen to disappear and reappear at irregular intervals,The witness described the object as silvery and brighter than familiar stars,The sighting involved observation of the motion relative to fixed stars in the sky.
sighted object: multiple bright objects moving between clouds
witness description: a civilian engaged in stellar observation before noticing the objects
